
@(Html.Kendo().DropDownList()
    .Name("newVehSeriesCode")
    .DataTextField("Text")
    .DataValueField("Value")
    .OptionLabel("-- Select Vehicle Series --")
    .DataSource(source =>
    {
        source.Read(read =>
        {
            read.Url("/AutoComplete/GetVehSeries"); // <-- add leading slash!
        });
    })
    .HtmlAttributes(new { style = "width:100%", required = "required" })
)

=====================================
üß© 1. Replace the textbox in your view (or editor template)

Change this line:

<input id="newVehSeriesCode" class="k-textbox" required />


to this:

@(Html.Kendo().DropDownList()
    .Name("newVehSeriesCode")
    .DataTextField("Text")        // display text
    .DataValueField("Value")      // actual value posted
    .OptionLabel("-- Select Vehicle Series --")
    .Filter("contains")
    .DataSource(source =>
    {
        source.Read(read =>
        {
            read.Action("GetVehSeries", "AutoComplete"); // Controller action
        })
        .ServerFiltering(false);
    })
    .HtmlAttributes(new { required = "required", style = "width:100%" })
)


üí° Tip:
Use .OptionLabel() to show a friendly default option, and .Filter("contains") if you want client-side filtering while typing.

üß† 2. Controller Action (AutoCompleteController.cs)

Your action should return a JSON list of items with Text and Value fields:

public IActionResult GetVehSeries()
{
    var seriesList = _vehicleService.GetAllSeries() // Example service call
        .Select(s => new 
        {
            Text = s.SeriesName,
            Value = s.SeriesCode
        });

    return Json(seriesList);
}


You can also use async if it‚Äôs pulling from a DB:

public async Task<IActionResult> GetVehSeries()
{
    var seriesList = await _vehicleService.GetAllSeriesAsync();
    return Json(seriesList.Select(s => new { Text = s.SeriesName, Value = s.SeriesCode }));
}

üß± 3. Move to a Shared Editor Template

If you want this dropdown reusable across views:

Create:
üìÅ /Views/Shared/EditorTemplates/VehicleSeriesDropDown.cshtml

Content:

@model string

@(Html.Kendo().DropDownListFor(m => m)
    .DataTextField("Text")
    .DataValueField("Value")
    .OptionLabel("-- Select Vehicle Series --")
    .Filter("contains")
    .DataSource(source =>
    {
        source.Read(read => read.Action("GetVehSeries", "AutoComplete"));
    })
    .HtmlAttributes(new { style = "width:100%", required = "required" })
)


Usage in any view:

@Html.EditorFor(model => model.NewVehSeriesCode, "VehicleSeriesDropDown")

üßæ 4. (Optional) Handle change event

If you want to auto-fill ‚ÄúNew Description‚Äù after a series is chosen:

$("#newVehSeriesCode").data("kendoDropDownList").bind("change", function (e) {
    var dataItem = this.dataItem();
    $("#newprojDesc").val(dataItem ? dataItem.Text : "");
});
